    <h2 class="ui dividing header">Introduction</h2>

    <h3 class="ui header">When To Use</h3>

    <div class="introduction">
      <p>A container is useful as a simpler alternative to a <a href="/collections/grid.html#page-grid">page grid</a> for holding page content. Containers have predetermined sizes and remain centered when there is additional space on large screens.</p>
      <p>Unlike a page grid, which continues to grow in size with larger screens using a percentage of screen width, containers maintain their size across a screen type, making content stay in the same position across all browser sizes for a device.</p>

      <p>The default theme uses a maximum container width of <code>1200px</code> which gives a <code>16 column ui grid</code> exactly <code>75px</code> per column when placed inside a container element.</p>

      <p>Containers have reasonable defaults designed to display page content, but you may need to adjust container sizes to fit your specific page content. For example, displaying railed content next to a container (like these docs use) may require you to include arbitrary resizes specific to your content.</p>

      <h3 class="ui header">Comparison of Features</h3>

      <table class="ui celled padded definition table">
        <thead>
          <th></th>
          <th class="six wide">Container</th>
          <th class="six wide">Page Grid</th>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Best Used With</td>
            <td>
              <ul class="ui list">
                <li>Pages using off-canvas content like <a href="/elements/rail.html">rails</a>, or fixed content.</li>
                <li>Text heavy pages that cannot accomodate fluid width resizes.</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
            <td>
              <ul class="ui list">
                <li>Highly polished, scalable content like homepages.</li>
                <li>Content with several columns</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Mobile</td>
            <td><code>100%</code> width, <code>1em</code> fixed gutter</td>
            <td><code>100%</code> width, <code>1em</code> fixed gutter</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Tablet</td>
            <td><code>768px</code> Centered</td>
            <td><code>100%</code> width, <code>2em</code> fixed gutter</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Computer</td>
            <td>
              <code>1040px</code> centered below <code>1228px</code>
              <div class="ui divider"></div>
